<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-11451] Don&apos;t mark sstables as repairing when doing sub range repair</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11451</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10422&quot; title=&quot;Avoid anticompaction when doing subrange repair&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10422&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10422&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we don&apos;t do anticompaction when a user issues a sub range repair (-st X -et Y), but we still mark sstables as repairing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should avoid marking them as users might want to run many sub range repair sessions in parallel. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason we mark sstables is that we don&apos;t want another repair session to steal the sstables before we do anticompaction, and since we do no anticompaction with sub range repair we have no benefit from the marking.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
